<item>
            <title>[SOLR-7781] FieldFaceting BytesRef reuse bug</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-7781</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;FieldFaceting on a string field has&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; TermQuery( &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; Term(field, bytesRef.clone() ) )
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The bytesRef needs to be deep copied (and clone() only implements a shallow copy).&lt;br/&gt;
This causes to the query inserted into the filter cache to be changed after the fact, and causes both cache misses and even cache growth way past configured limits due to failures to remove old cache items (&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-7777&quot; title=&quot;FastLRUCache size keeps growing if query is changed after insertion&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-7777&quot;&gt;SOLR-7777&lt;/a&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
